## Implementation order

```
Phase 1.1–1.2  Split prompts + cache_control     ← highest ROI
Phase 2.1        Context dedupe + token cap
Phase 2.2        History trim
Phase 4.1        Real usage metrics
Phase 1.4        Golden-set validation
Phase 3.1        Follow-up skip rules
Phase 3.2        Prompt consolidation
Phase 5          Routing + max_tokens tuning
```

---

## Per-request token budget (target state)

| Segment | Target tokens | Cached? |
|---------|-------------:|---------|
| Static instructions | ~450 | Yes |
| Retrieved docs | 2,000–4,000 | No |
| History | ≤1,500 | No |
| User query | ≤200 | No |
| **Total input** | **~3,000–6,000** | partial |
| Output (Haiku) | ≤1,200 | — |
| Output (Sonnet) | ≤3,000 | — |

Down from ~5,000–8,000+ input today on heavy turns.

---

## Risks & mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| Cache min size not met (Haiku 1024 tokens) | Pad static block with product reference appendix from `prompts.py` |
| LangChain streaming + cache_control bugs | Test direct `AsyncAnthropic` fallback path |
| Quality regression on Sonnet→Haiku shifts | Golden set + LangSmith diffs before routing changes |
| History trim breaks follow-ups | Keep `_contextualize_query()` + last user message always |

---

## Quick wins (can ship independently)

1. Trim history to last 6 turns
2. Dedupe retrieved chunks by `s3_key`
3. Skip follow-ups on blocked responses
4. Log real `usage` from Anthropic responses
5. Set `MAX_RETRIEVAL_RESULTS=8` on Railway if currently 15

